g.aria-label: If you are not at the edge of the neighborhood (i.e. if you are at a 4-way intersection rather than a 2-way or 3-way intersection), go to step 5. You must be quite familiar with the neighborhood by now -- you've driven past every block except two! ("Driven past" means that you drove on a road forming one of the edges of that square; for example, when you drove three blocks forward in the beginning, you drove past the three blocks that were to your right.) Plot a course for the nearest block you haven't driven past -- take the shortest path that drives past that block while only turning once (including turns from your current orientation).
